HEADWORD: Substitutive
<hw>Sub"sti*tu`tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>substitutif</ets>, L. <ets>substitutivus</ets> conditional.]</ety>
<def>Tending to afford or furnish a substitute; making substitution;
capable of being substituted.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Wilkins.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
